default4)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default 
defaultResulting problems for the local community
default:
default&#xa0;
defaultYoung people 
defaultunable to access after school activities, no transport home.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultPeople out of work, school leavers, work placement people, those struggling with poor mental health issues and those wit
defaulth physical and learning disabilities  - an efficient transport system would increase access to work opportunities for them.
default&#xa0;
default18-25 year olds have to pay a high premium for car insurance which restricts those who might have a car. The young who do not live 
defaultin towns are severely limited in their access to work, cultural activities and socialising. 
default&#xa0;
defaultFamilies – affected by cost of keeping a car on the road, eg  a two car family having to give up one car resulting in limitations on access to out of school activ
defaultities.
default&#xa0;
defaultAble bodied adults who are non drivers have to rely on neighbours or expensive taxi services to travel into Llandovery, eg  £30 return fare from Rhandirmwyn to Llandovery
default – a distance of seven miles.
default&#xa0;
defaultAdults with mobility problems are dependant on 
defaultothers being able to visit them for social and caring services.
default 
