default5)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default 
defaultSuggested solutions
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultBuses  - increase the number of services to
default include evenings 
default&#xa0;
defaultTrains – add one extra service per day in each direction
default at appropriate times.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultTransport links – 
defaultrealistic co-ordination of timetables, this should be feasible as both buses and trains are operated by Arriva.
default&#xa0;
defaultLinks to nearby villages – introduce a dial-up request mini-bus service.
defaultA service entitled Bwcabus operates in the western half of the county 
defaultonly. 
default&#xa0;
defaultRural areas require direct buses linking town to town centres, with feeder minibuses from surrounding villages. 
defaultThe times of trains and buses should facilitate work in the mornings and socialising in the evenings. 
